sorry if this is a duplicate - I couldn't find an issue mentioning it.

when finding issues, if the user picker is used (by choosing "specify user" for one of the user id inputs), and in the resulting popup, a filter is applied, clicking on the pager numbers at the bottom always resets the filter.

I believe the error is in ..web.action.admin.user.UserPickerBrowser - resetPager() is called in the doExecute() method.  Instead, it should be called in doDefault() and only if the filter is changed:

   public String doDefault()
   throws Exception {
      resetPager();
      return "success";
   }

   protected String doExecute()
   throws Exception
   {
      // do not call this every time:
      // resetPager();

      BeanUtil.setProperties(params, getFilter());

      // If the user changes either the email filter, name filter or the group,
      // reset the cursor to the start of the filter result set.
      if (params.containsKey("emailFilter") || params.containsKey("group") || params.containsKey("nameFilter"))
      {
         resetPager();
         setStart("0");
      }

      return super.doExecute();
   }
